# Design doc conventions

## Prerequisite

A design doc requires an existing PRD in `thoughts/prds/`. Link to it in the opening paragraph.

## File naming

`MM-DD-YYYY-topic.md` (e.g. `04-04-2026-app-shell-layout.md`)

## Required structure

```markdown
# Title (design)

Companion to the PRD ([link](../prds/MM-DD-YYYY-topic-prd.md)). Brief description of what this design covers.

---

## Purpose
## [Component/Area sections with tables and behavior descriptions]
## Implementation note (current repo vs PRD)
```

**Key rules:**
- Open with a one-liner linking to the PRD and stating scope
- Use **tables** for tab order, component behavior, responsive specs
- Describe interaction patterns (tap, scroll, navigation) not pixel values
- Reference PRD sections by symbol (e.g. "PRD section 5.4")
- Include a **Native vs web** section when behavior diverges
- End with an **Implementation note** bridging current repo state to target
- Use Tamagui token names (`$background`, `$color2`, `$space`) not raw values
